results.abstract: Moscow press repts Otvazhnaya will soon try 6th flight; says movies during last flight show her calm

headline.main: SOVIET ROCKET DOG SET FOR 6th FLIGHT

results.snippet: MOSCOW, July 6 -- The Soviet Union's most traveled canine astronaut, a fluffy white mutt called Otvazhnaya, or Courageous, soon will be ready to start training for her sixth rocket flight into the upper atmosphere, Moscow newspapers reported today.

results.lead_paragraph: FASTER PROTONS -- The world's most powerful atomic accelerator, at the Brookhaven National Laboratory of the Atomic Energy Commission, started operation Friday afternoon with a cascade of energy which accelerated protons (nuclei of hydrogen atoms) to more than 30 billion electronvolts, the greatest acceleration so far achieved anywhere on earth by a man-made machine.
